3.0 of 5 bubbles
Overhyped, overcrowded, and polluted
Jan 2019 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We did a ‚Äúluxury‚Äù 2-day cruise around Halong Bay, Lan Ha Bay and the Cat Ba island. It was pretty expensive for what you actually get. In reality, it‚Äôs only a 24-hr cruise, not 2 days, and we spent more on 1-night cruise than on all of our accommodation in Vietnam for 3-weeks we were there. Was it worth it?! Definitely not!!!

Halong Bay is not as pretty as you see in magazines - photos that are heavily edited to make it look amazing. The place is overcrowded by tourists, as a result it is extremely polluted. There are plastic bags floating in the water, and a permanent smog surrounds the mountains preventing any clear views. No, it‚Äôs not clouds, it‚Äôs pollution from all of the boats around the area. I was unpleasantly surprised by how polluted this place was as I was expecting a natural beauty (which was undoubtedly there maybe 10-20 years ago but is now being destroyed by excessive tourism).
If I had to do it all over again, I wouldn‚Äôt.
If you, however, want a great alternative to Halong Bay, authentic and uncrowded beauty with equally impressive limestone cliffs, then you should head to Ninh Binh or Phong Nha - the places that still retain a lot of charm and authenticity of Vietnam. I wish someone would have advised me against coming to Halong Bay as I would have gladly extended my stays in both aforementioned places or gone to Sapa.
If you are desperate to see it, then go to Cat Ba island and book a tour from there. It will be much cheaper, and the bay around that area is much quieter.
The problem with overnight cruises is that they are super expensive for a relatively average experience. The rooms are nice, but would we really pay several hundreds of dollars for a nice hotel room for one night in Vietnam, where we were able to get a lovely room (of the same standard) in the center of Hanoi old town for $25?! Even 5-star cruises are still tourist factories - they get you in, they get you out as quickly as possible, because they are readying the boat for new guests the next day. There is no personalised experience that many of them claim they offer.
If you want a truly magnificent views with limestone cliffs and crystal clear waters - go to Coron Town or El Nido in Philippines instead. Now that‚Äôs a view I will never forget!
Written January 16, 2019
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
