1.0 of 5 bubbles
Pollution is overwhelming
Feb 2018 ‚Ä¢ Couples
While in Vietnam we did the obligatory visit to Halong Bay. Yuk!
We flew to Halong Bay by SeaPlane which was the best part of the trip, simply because you get to view the enormity of the bay and pinnacles.
But the air and water pollution are so bad that it ends up being a trip to view how a Country can contaminate and ruin a natural wonder.
We were dropped at a beach to go for a swim..... but I‚Äôm not keen on swimming with babies nappies, sanitary pads and condoms not to mention the festering scum that floats on top of the water.
The air is so thick with pollution that if you suffer with a respiratory issue ie. asthma..... then be careful. The guides try to make out it‚Äôs a sea haze, just like they do in China. But the funny part is that, just like in China the sky starts to clear in patches by Sunday afternoon. One guide even tried telling us that it was China‚Äôs pollution not theirs.
I‚Äôve travelled extensively and can tell you that you can get better scenery than this in Thailand, off Phuket there are an enclave of pinnacle islands. The water is pristine, the air is clear, no pollution, the beaches are golden - no rubbish, you can see the sun, stars and the moon. We stayed at the island of Ko Yao Noi, Thailand and there was no comparison.
If your travel money is tight, do yourself a favour and compare. Or just look at my photos and know that this is what Halong Bay really looks like.... Grey, Dull and Polluted.
Written March 31, 2018
