5.0 of 5 bubbles
Well worth it!
Nov 2017 ‚Ä¢ Family
Alot of reviews mentioned that Ha Long Bay needs to be enjoyed by staying overnight. However due to time constraints I did a full day trip from 730 am till about 930 pm. It sounded long and tiring but with our exceptional tour guide Kien from the newly formed Dragon King Travel, we enjoyed every single minute of it. The coach is very new with wifi and charging ports and as it drives past the different provinces Kien talks about their culture. He is able to get our group to mingle around and we had a relaxing time cruising the bay, eating and drinking and making new friends. This company goes on the longer route to see Surprising Cave ( the biggest). We get to kayak around an enclave and climb Ti top mountain to have a panoramic view of the bay. As we cruise into the sunset we are even served red wine! Go to Dragon King Travel Facebook page to ask them for their price so you will bypass the numerous travel agents in Hanoi.
