Polluted.
Jun 2017 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We did a 2 day, 1 night tour of Halong Bay. We wasn't sure on going here as we thought it would be polluted and busy with tourist boats but we thought we should just because it is a UNESCO world heritage site and it would be a shame to come all the way to Vietnam and skip it.
It is an incredible place, There is no denying, however our thoughts on why we should have skipped it were true. It is completely ruined with waste, plastics, packing foam and so on and after visiting the Philippines we couldnt help compare the two places. The Philippines is absolutely beautiful and Halong Bay just wasn't. There are too many boats on the waters pumping out black smoke into the air and Its disgusting.
We stopped at a lagoon to kayak and ended up litter picking because there was so much plastic floating around. When we took the kayak back the guys running the kayaking just pushed the boat back out with the others and left the pile of rubbish on the boat. Real nice.
The Vietnamese have a total disregard for their environment and you will see this when/If you come here. Such a shame.
Written June 28, 2017
John J
North Yorkshire, UK714 contributions
Polluted Bay
Aug 2016
We stayed 4 nights on Cat Ba Island which is part of a chain of 366 islands that lie within the larger area of Ha Long bay.
Famous for stunning natural beauty it was officially recognized as a World Biosphere Reserve
It attracts millions of visitors from around the world.
However, it is cluttered with litter everywhere - Yes everywhere and I have never swam / canoed in open seas (and snorkel) where there are no fishes. None.
The whole area is over fished and much worse - grossly polluted.
Unbelievable disgrace, a disaster of Global proportions and the Vietnamese peoples should be very ashamed!
Action needs to be taken urgently to recover and then preserve this natural beauty.
Written September 10, 2016
Elizaveta E
